Colouration.
Tegmina transparent with a very characteristic colour pattern: dark patches arranged in longitudinal stripes (
Figs. 5J, K
). Body mainly dark (
Figs. 5
A–I, N), with some lighter coloured areas: A narrow interocular stripe on the head, thoracal nota with broad transparent margins, legs for most part ochre, narrow whitish stripe along the lateral and posterior borders of tergites and the lateral borders of sternites. Lightly coloured areas often further extended, especially in females (
Fig. 5O, P
). Disk of pronotum often reddish (
Fig. 5O
), sometimes of all nota.
